# NYXUS · airootfs gitignore — rev 2026-05-09 r3 (Option A switch + system override)
#
# HISTORICAL: this file used to exclude usr/local/bin/, opt/nyxus-intel/,
# usr/share/applications/, and etc/skel/.config/ because the old build flow
# extracted them at bake time from tarballs. That strategy was abandoned —
# we now pre-stage everything into airootfs/ and let archiso copy the tree
# directly. ALL of those paths must be tracked by git or build-iso.sh
# clones a tree without the launcher and mkarchiso fails with
# "Failed to set permissions ... Outside of valid path".
#
# IMPORTANT: the Replit container ships a system-wide /etc/.gitignore that
# excludes `.config/`, `.local/`, `.cache/`, `__pycache__/`, etc. Those rules
# would silently drop airootfs/etc/skel/.config/* from any commit. The
# negation block below re-includes the skel tree so it actually ships.

# Re-include the skel .config tree (system /etc/.gitignore excludes .config/).
# Negation rules must un-ignore the directory FIRST, then its contents,
# otherwise git prunes the dir before recursing.
!etc/skel/.config/
!etc/skel/.config/**

# Local-only cruft we still want excluded
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.swp
*~
.DS_Store
